  "prompt": "How do I Download Pokken Tournament for PC?",
  "response": "As of my last update, \"Pokk\u00e9n Tournament\" is not officially available for PC. It was released for the Wii U and later for the Nintendo Switch as \"Pokk\u00e9n Tournament DX.\" Since it's a Nintendo-published game, it's unlikely to be officially released on PC platforms due to Nintendo's typical exclusivity policies.\n\nHowever, if you're interested in playing similar games on your PC, here are a few alternatives you might consider:\n\n1. **Tekken 7**: This is a popular fighting game developed by Bandai Namco, the same company that developed Pokk\u00e9n Tournament. It's available on PC and offers a similar fighting game experience.\n\n2. **Brawlhalla**: A free-to-play platform fighting game available on PC, which, while different in style, offers engaging combat and is frequently updated with new content.\n\n3. **Naruto Shippuden: Ultimate Ninja STORM 4**: Another fighting game with anime-style characters, available on PC, which might appeal if you enjoy the character-based combat of Pokk\u00e9n Tournament.\n\nIf you're looking for ways to play \"Pokk\u00e9n Tournament\" specifically, your only official option is to purchase a Nintendo Switch and buy \"Pokk\u00e9n Tournament DX.\" Be cautious of any unofficial sources claiming to offer the game for PC, as these could be illegal or unsafe.\n\nKeep an eye on official channels from Nintendo and Bandai Namco for any potential future announcements regarding PC releases, though such an event would be highly unusual given current trends.",
